        <p>Converts the cursor to Arrow mode, which lets you create a curvy arrow shape. After you select this button, you can click anywhere in the image to identify the starting point for the arrow. When you move the cursor, a straight line shows where the arrow will be placed. When you release the cursor, an arrow is created. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Capture/Interface/Dialogs/Arrow-Properties-Dialog.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Arrow Properties Dialog</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
